Answer: They are similar because when I increase the bin size; there are more gaps between points. Mjage is skewed right and iralcage looks like its skewed (slightly?) to the left. Mjage also looks like its unimodal while iralcage looks almost bimodal, as there are two tall points surrounded by less tall points. 6. (5 points) Do visual EDA for irsex and sexatract. What do you learn from this?

# Note: This line makes the levels of the factors take on the values from the codebook. Run it before you make your plots to have clearer labels.

dat <- dat %>%
  mutate_at(c('irsex', 'sexatract', 'speakengl'), as.factor) %>%
  mutate(irsex = recode(irsex,         "1"="Male", "2"="Female"),
         sexatract = recode(sexatract, "1"="I am only attracted to opposite sex",
                                       "2"="I am mostly attracted to opposite sex",
                                       "3"="I am equally attracted to males and females",
                                       "4"="I am mostly attracted to same sex",
                                       "5"="I am only attracted to same sex",
                                       "6"="I am not sure",
                                       "99"="Legitimate skip"),
         speakengl = recode(speakengl, "1"="Very well",
                                       "2"="Well",
                                       "3"="Not well",
                                       "4"="Not at all"))

#visual eda irsex

dat %>% 
  ggplot(aes(irsex)) + 
  geom_bar()

#visual EDA sexatract

dat %>% 
  ggplot(aes(sexatract)) + 
  geom_bar()

#i made one for speakengl too because the next question asks something abt it and i didnt know where to stick it
dat %>% 
  ggplot(aes(speakengl)) + 
  geom_bar()

Answer: l learned that for irsex, it only seems like there is a pretty even distribution as only a slightly larger number of men than women that are recorded, and for seattract there seems to be a very amount of people only are attracted to the opposite sex, as opposed to the minuscule amounts for the other variables. this can indicate that most people in this dataset that are recorded are heterosexual and may be more likely to be a man than a woman.

The colors are helpful in order to figure out the propotion of the peoples attatacttion during the onset of their marijuanan usage
